The Internet is a web of cables, primarily optical fiber cables, through which data is transmitted.

Internet Infrastructure Explained:

‚úÖ Tier 1 ‚Äì Companies that own undersea fiber-optic cables and lease them to others. be proud TATA is one of them .These cables run across land and oceans, facilitating global connectivity. (B2B Model)

‚úÖ Tier 2 ‚Äì Providers like BSNL, Jio, and others who purchase bandwidth from Tier 1 companies to distribute further. (B2B Model)

‚úÖ Tier 3 ‚Äì Service providers such as Jio Fiber, Airtel Fiber, and You Broadband that deliver internet to end-users (homes & businesses). (B2C Model)

